properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 31 at 8:29AM PST until February 1 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Pendleton OR
properties.description:
...BREEZY TO GUSTY WINDS TODAY AND TOMORROW...

.Southerly winds are building in the Grande Ronde Valley. These
will continue through today and into tonight. Blue Mountain
foothills may see breezy southerlies this evening before a broad
area of breezy to gusty winds overspread much of the Columbia
Basin Saturday.

* WHAT...South winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 50 mph
expected For Ladd and Pyles Canyons.

* WHERE...Southern Grande Ronde Valley.

* WHEN...Until noon PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...High profile vehicles traveling I-84 and other area
roads should exercise caution. Gusty winds could blow around
unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few
power outages may result.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON PST SATURDAY FOR LADD AND PYLES CANYONS
